.TH "sshp_validate_crc" 9 "sshp_validate_crc" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
sshp_validate_crc \- Validate a CRC in raw message data.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" sshp_validate_crc
.BI "(const struct ssam_span *src "  ","
.BI "const u8 *crc "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "src" 12
The span of data over which the CRC should be computed.
.IP "crc" 12
The pointer to the expected u16 CRC value.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Computes the CRC of the provided data span (\fIsrc\fP), compares it to the CRC
stored at the given address (\fIcrc\fP), and returns the result of this
comparison, i.e. true if equal. This function is intended to run on raw
input/message data.
.SH "RETURN"
Returns true if the computed CRC matches the stored CRC, false
otherwise.
